# Preserve Existing Comments

**NEVER remove or modify existing code comments** unless the comment is
factually wrong due to your changes (e.g. it describes behavior that no
longer exists after your edit).

- If a comment is above code you are editing, keep it as-is.
- If a comment is inside a block you are refactoring, carry it over.
- Do not "clean up" comments you consider redundant or obvious.
- Do not rephrase comments to match your style preferences.
- The only valid reason to touch a comment is if your code change makes
  the comment factually incorrect.

This is a hard rule. Violations are unacceptable.
